<A NAME="270"><H3><STRONG>Small Business Development Centers </STRONG></H3></A>
Small Business Development Centers are state funded resource centers, administered by the Minnesota Small Business Assistance Office, which provide information and counseling to small businesses and persons wanting to start small businesses. In order to qualify for assistance, a business must meet the definition of a "small business" set by the federal Small Business Administration.
